{"title_page": "Lymphomatoid papulosis", "text_new": "{{Refimprove|date=January 2009}}\n{{Infobox medical condition (new) \n| name            = Lymphomatoid papulosis \n| image           =  \n| caption         =  \n| \n| pronounce       =  \n| field           =  \n| synonyms        =  \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Lymphomatoid papulosis''' ('''LyP''') is a rare [[skin disorder]]. The overall prevalence rate of lymphomatoid papulosis is estimated at 1.2 to 1.9 cases per 1,000,000 population. This rare condition has only been studied in depth since 1968.<ref name=\"pmid5634442\">{{cite journal |author=Macaulay WL |title=Lymphomatoid papulosis. A continuing self-healing eruption, clinically benign--histologically malignant |journal=Arch Dermatol |volume=97 |issue=1 |pages=23\u201330 |date=January 1968 |pmid=5634442 |doi= 10.1001/archderm.97.1.23|url=}}</ref>\n\n==Presentation==\nIt can appear very similar to [[anaplastic large cell lymphoma]].<ref name=\"pmid15096372\">{{cite journal |vauthors=El Shabrawi-Caelen L, Kerl H, Cerroni L |title=Lymphomatoid papulosis: reappraisal of clinicopathologic presentation and classification into subtypes A, B, and C |journal=Arch Dermatol |volume=140 |issue=4 |pages=441\u20137 |date=April 2004 |pmid=15096372 |doi=10.1001/archderm.140.4.441 |url=http://archderm.ama-assn.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=15096372 }}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\nType \"A\" is [[CD30]] positive, while type \"B\" is CD30 negative.<ref name=\"YoungGerson2006\">{{cite book|author1=Neal S. Young|author2=Stanton L. Gerson|author3=Katherine A. High|title=Clinical hematology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LY93_9iBb_IC&pg=PA555|accessdate=14 May 2011|year=2006|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|isbn=978-0-323-01908-8|pages=555\u2013}}</ref>\n\nIt has been described as \"clinically benign but histologically malignant.\"<ref name=\"Proytcheva2011\">{{cite book|author=Maria Proytcheva|title=Diagnostic Pediatric Hematopathology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8s8stgvB1kUC&pg=PA544|accessdate=15 May 2011|date=14 March 2011|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-88160-9|pages=544\u2013}}</ref>\n\n==Cause==\n{{Empty section|date=June 2017}}\n==Diagnosis==\n{{Empty section|date=June 2017}}\n\n==Treatment==\nIt may respond to [[methotrexate]] or PUVA.<ref name=\"pmid16627259\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Magro CM, Crowson AN, Morrison C, Merati K, Porcu P, Wright ED |title=CD8+ lymphomatoid papulosis and its differential diagnosis |journal=Am. J. Clin. Pathol. |volume=125 |issue=4 |pages=490\u2013501 |date=April 2006 |pmid=16627259 |doi=10.1309/NNV4-L5G5-A0KF-1T06 |url=http://ajcp.metapress.com/openurl.asp?genre=article&doi=10.1309/NNV4-L5G5-A0KF-1T06}}</ref>\n\n==Prognosis==\nIt can evolve into [[lymphoma]].<ref name=\"pmid16638423\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Dalle S, Balme B, Thomas L |title=Lymphomatoid papulosis localized to the face |journal=Dermatol. Online J. |volume=12 |issue=3 |pages=9 |year=2006 |pmid=16638423 |doi= |url=http://dermatology.cdlib.org/123/case_reports/lymphomatoid/dalle.html}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Cutaneous T-cell lymphoma]]\n* [[Parapsoriasis]]\n* [[Secondary cutaneous CD30+ large cell lymphoma]]\n* [[List of cutaneous conditions]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n| DiseasesDB      = 33778\n| ICD10           = {{ICD10|L|41|2|l|40}}\n| ICD9            = \n| ICDO            = 9718/1\n| OMIM            = \n| MedlinePlus     = \n| eMedicineSubj   = derm\n| eMedicineTopic  = 254\n| MeshID          = D017731\n| SNOMED CT       = 31047003\n| Orphanet        = 98842\n}}\n{{Hematological malignancy histology}}\n{{Papulosquamous disorders}}\n\n[[Category:Rare diseases]]\n[[Category:Lymphoid-related cutaneous conditions]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=January 2009}}\n{{Infobox medical condition (new) \n| name            = Lymphomatoid papulosis \n| image           =  \n| caption         =  \n| \n| pronounce       =  \n| field           =  \n| synonyms        =  \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Lymphomatoid papulosis''' ('''LyP''') is a rare [[skin disorder]]. The overall prevalence rate of lymphomatoid papulosis is estimated at 1.2 to 1.9 cases per 1,000,000 population. This rare condition has only been studied in depth since 1968.<ref name=\"pmid5634442\">{{cite journal |author=Macaulay WL |title=Lymphomatoid papulosis. A continuing self-healing eruption, clinically benign--histologically malignant |journal=Arch Dermatol |volume=97 |issue=1 |pages=23\u201330 |date=January 1968 |pmid=5634442 |doi= 10.1001/archderm.97.1.23|url=}}</ref>\n\n==Presentation==\nIt can appear very similar to [[anaplastic large cell lymphoma]].<ref name=\"pmid15096372\">{{cite journal |vauthors=El Shabrawi-Caelen L, Kerl H, Cerroni L |title=Lymphomatoid papulosis: reappraisal of clinicopathologic presentation and classification into subtypes A, B, and C |journal=Arch Dermatol |volume=140 |issue=4 |pages=441\u20137 |date=April 2004 |pmid=15096372 |doi=10.1001/archderm.140.4.441 |url=http://archderm.ama-assn.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=15096372 }}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\nType \"A\" is [[CD30]] positive, while type \"B\" is CD30 negative.<ref name=\"YoungGerson2006\">{{cite book|author1=Neal S. Young|author2=Stanton L. Gerson|author3=Katherine A. High|title=Clinical hematology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LY93_9iBb_IC&pg=PA555|accessdate=14 May 2011|year=2006|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|isbn=978-0-323-01908-8|pages=555\u2013}}</ref>\n\nIt has been described as \"clinically benign but histologically malignant.\"<ref name=\"Proytcheva2011\">{{cite book|author=Maria Proytcheva|title=Diagnostic Pediatric Hematopathology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8s8stgvB1kUC&pg=PA544|accessdate=15 May 2011|date=14 March 2011|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-88160-9|pages=544\u2013}}</ref>\n\n==Cause==\n{{Empty section|date=June 2017}}\n==Diagnosis==\n{{Empty section|date=June 2017}}\n\n==Treatment==\nIt may respond to [[methotrexate]] or PUVA.<ref name=\"pmid16627259\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Magro CM, Crowson AN, Morrison C, Merati K, Porcu P, Wright ED |title=CD8+ lymphomatoid papulosis and its differential diagnosis |journal=Am. J. Clin. Pathol. |volume=125 |issue=4 |pages=490\u2013501 |date=April 2006 |pmid=16627259 |doi=10.1309/NNV4-L5G5-A0KF-1T06 |url=http://ajcp.metapress.com/openurl.asp?genre=article&doi=10.1309/NNV4-L5G5-A0KF-1T06}}</ref>\n\n==Prognosis==\nIt can evolve into [[lymphoma]].<ref name=\"pmid16638423\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Dalle S, Balme B, Thomas L |title=Lymphomatoid papulosis localized to the face |journal=Dermatol. Online J. |volume=12 |issue=3 |pages=9 |year=2006 |pmid=16638423 |doi= |url=http://dermatology.cdlib.org/123/case_reports/lymphomatoid/dalle.html}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Cutaneous T-cell lymphoma]]\n* [[Parapsoriasis]]\n* [[Secondary cutaneous CD30+ large cell lymphoma]]\n* [[List of cutaneous conditions]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n|   DiseasesDB     = 33778 \n|   ICD10          = {{ICD10|L|41|2|l|40}} \n|   ICD9           = \n|   ICDO           = 9718/1 \n|   OMIM           = \n|   MedlinePlus    = \n|   eMedicineSubj  = derm \n|   eMedicineTopic = 254 \